# Design System Rules

Apply these rules whenever touching frontend or shared UI code (`frontend`, `packages/ui`):

1. Use shadcn as the primary component source before building custom UI primitives.
2. Use Tailwind CSS as the primary styling system; avoid ad-hoc CSS when utilities or design tokens cover the need.
3. Prefer composing existing shadcn components over creating new parallel component APIs.
4. Build the co-editing workspace with reusable layout primitives (cards, separators, tabs, alerts, inputs, buttons) from shadcn.
5. Keep interaction states consistent across chat and document panes (loading, streaming, approval pending, error).
